  "prompt": "What's the best residential ISP in San Francisco?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several Internet Service Providers (ISPs) are notable in San Francisco, and the \"best\" option can vary based on individual needs such as speed, price, customer service, and availability. Here are some of the top ISPs in the area:\n\n1. **Xfinity (Comcast)**: Offers high-speed cable internet with various plans. Xfinity is known for its fast download speeds and wide coverage.\n\n2. **AT&T**: Provides both fiber optic (AT&T Fiber) and DSL internet services. AT&T Fiber is known for its high speed and reliability, especially in urban areas.\n\n3. **Sonic**: A smaller, local ISP that offers fiber and DSL services. Sonic is known for excellent customer service and competitive pricing, especially for fiber services.\n\n4. **Wave Broadband**: Also offers cable internet services with competitive speeds and pricing, though availability can vary by neighborhood.\n\n5. **Verizon Fios**: While it may not be as widely available, Verizon offers fiber services with high speeds and good reliability where it operates.\n\nWhen choosing an ISP, consider factors like speed requirements, costs, contract terms, customer service, and the specific availability in your area. Checking local reviews and using tools like broadband map websites can also help you make an informed decision.",
